\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 5. Authentication and Authorization\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 5.1 Google Ads API authentication\b0\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa120\b Developer Token:\b0  Stored in GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN (server environment variable).\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b OAuth 2.0 Client ID / Secret:\b0  Stored in GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Refresh Token:\b0  Obtained once via local OAuth flow (scripts/google-ads-auth.js); stored in GOOGLE_ADS_REFRESH_TOKEN. Used server-side to obtain short-lived access tokens.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Customer ID:\b0  GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID = 4701190207 (VouRifar MCC / advertising account).\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Login Customer ID:\b0  GOOGLE_ADS_LOGIN_CUSTOMER_ID = 4701190207 (manager account context).\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b 5.2 OAuth flow (one-time setup)\b0\par
1. Administrator runs npm run google-ads:auth on a secure machine.\par
2. Local HTTP server listens on localhost:8765/callback.\par
3. Administrator authorizes via Google OAuth consent screen (scope: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adwords).\par
4. Authorization code is exchanged for refresh token; token is saved to server .env.\par
5. Refresh token is never transmitted to end users or stored in client-side code.\par
\par
\b 5.3 Application access control\b0\par
Only authenticated super-admin sessions can trigger Google Ads operations. Admin routes are protected by session middleware and role checks. API credentials remain on the server at all times.\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 6. Google Ads API Operations Used\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1
We plan to use the following Google Ads API services and methods (API version v22):\par
\par
\b 6.1 Read operations (GoogleAdsService.Search / SearchStream)\b0\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa120 List accessible customers (customers:listAccessibleCustomers)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Query campaigns: id, name, status, budget, bidding strategy\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Query ad groups: id, name, status, campaign association\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Query ads: responsive search ad headlines, descriptions, final URLs\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Query keywords: text, match type, status\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Query performance metrics: impressions, clicks, cost_micros, conversions (campaign and ad group level)\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b 6.2 Write operations (GoogleAdsService.Mutate)\b0\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa120 Create CampaignBudget\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Create Campaign (type: SEARCH)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Create AdGroup\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Create AdGroupCriterion (keywords)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Create AdGroupAd (ResponsiveSearchAd)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Update campaign/ad group/ad status (ENABLED / PAUSED)\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Update campaign budget amounts\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b 6.3 Campaign types supported\b0\par
\b Search campaigns only.\b0  We do not plan to use Shopping, Display, Video, Performance Max, or App campaigns at this time.\par
\par
\b 6.4 Geographic and language targeting\b0\par
Brazil (country code BR), Portuguese language ads, BRL currency.\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 7. Data Flow\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 7.1 Campaign creation flow\b0\par
1. Administrator submits campaign parameters in super-admin UI (name, daily budget, keywords, ad copy, landing URL).\par
2. VouRifar server validates input and builds MutateOperation requests.\par
3. Server obtains access token via refresh token exchange.\par
4. Server sends mutate request to Google Ads API with developer-token and login-customer-id headers.\par
5. Google returns resource names; server stores campaign mapping in internal logs (optional).\par
6. Administrator sees confirmation and campaign ID in admin dashboard.\par
\par
\b 7.2 Reporting flow\b0\par
1. Scheduled job or manual action triggers GAQL query for date range.\par
2. Server retrieves metrics via SearchStream.\par
3. Metrics displayed in super-admin dashboard; no data is sold or shared externally.\par
\par
\b 7.3 Data retention\b0\par
Performance snapshots may be cached in the application database for up to 90 days for internal analytics. OAuth tokens and developer token are stored only in encrypted server environment configuration. No Google Ads data is exposed to tenant organizers or public API endpoints.\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 8. Expected API Usage Volume\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1
Estimated daily operations (well within Basic Access limits of 15,000 operations/day and 1,000 get operations/day):\par
\par
\b Activity\b0\tab\b Est. operations/day\b0\par
Campaign creation (manual)\tab 10\'9650\par
Campaign status/budget updates\tab 20\'96100\par
Performance reporting queries\tab 50\'96200\par
Connection health checks\tab 1\'965\par
\b Total estimated\b0\tab\b 100\'96350 operations/day\b0\par
\par
We do not anticipate requiring Standard Access in the foreseeable future.\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 9. Error Handling and Monitoring\b0\fs22\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa120 HTTP errors and GoogleAdsFailure details are logged server-side with request ID.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Transient errors (429, 5xx) use exponential backoff with a maximum of 3 retries.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Invalid mutate requests are rejected before API call via input validation.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}OAuth token refresh failures alert administrators via application logs.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Daily connection test available via npm run google-ads:test.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 10. Security and Compliance\b0\fs22\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa120\b Internal use only:\b0  Tool is not distributed to clients or resold.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Credential isolation:\b0  All Google Ads credentials stored server-side; never in client JavaScript or mobile apps.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Access control:\b0  Super-admin authentication required for all campaign operations.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Policy compliance:\b0  Ads promote VouRifar\'92s legitimate SaaS platform (raffle management software), not individual gambling or lottery products. Landing pages comply with Google Ads policies.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b No third-party token sharing:\b0  Developer token is used exclusively for VouRifar\'92s own advertising account.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

